EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO LABOR AND LABOR RELATIONS -- CONSUMER CREDIT HISTORY
EMPLOYMENT PROTECTION ACT -- DECEPTIVE TRADE PRACTICES
***
1 This act would prohibit employers from seeking or using credit reports in making hiring
2 decisions concerning prospective employees, asking questions about the applicant's financial past
3 during its interviews, or including credit history questions within the applicant's job applications.
4 It would authorize the department of labor and training to impose administrative fines against the
5 offending employer. Finally, it would also allow the aggrieved employee to seek civil financial
6 damages and attorneys' fees.
7 This act would take effect upon passage.
